DeviceFailure.description: At least one of the top-level Assets has its DeviceHealth set to Failure.

DeviceCheckFunction.description: At least one of the top-level Assets has its DeviceHealth set to CheckFunction.

DeviceMaintenanceRequired.description: At least one of the top-level Assets has its DeviceHealth set to MaintenanceRequired.

DeviceOffSpec.description: At least one of the top-level Assets has its DeviceHealth set to OffSpec.

SubOperationalWarning.description: One of the SubFunctionalEntities indicates a warning.

FxCommandMask.description: This OptionSet defines flags indicating the commands a ConnectionManager may use in its call to the EstablishConnections Method.

VerifyAssetCmd.description: The addressed Server shall verify compatibility and/or identity for all requested Assets.

VerifyFunctionalEntityCmd.description: The addressed Server shall verify compatibility for all requested functional entities.

CreateConnectionEndpointCmd.description: The addressed Server shall create or modify ConnectionEndpoints.

EstablishControlCmd.description: The addressed Server shall establish control over the requested ControlGroups.

SetConfigurationDataCmd.description: The addressed Server shall apply the supplied application configuration.

ReassignControlCmd.description: The addressed Server shall reassign the requested ControlGroups.

ReserveCommunicationIdsCmd.description: The addressed Server shall reserve identifiers for the communication model configuration.

SetCommunicationConfigurationCmd.description: The addressed Server shall apply the supplied communication model configuration.

EnableCommunicationCmd.description: The addressed Server shall enable the communication configuration.

ConnectionEndpointStatusEnum.description: This enumeration defines the values of the FlcConnectionStatus of an FlcConnectionEndpointType.

Initial.description: Initial status of the logical connection. No communication-model objects referenced.

Ready.description: Logical connection is ready to operate, Communication-model objects are referenced but not enabled.

PreOperational.description: PreOperational status of the logical connection, Data output is active, but no input data received.

Operational.description: Operational status of the logical connection, Data output is active, and input data has been received.

Error.description: The logical connection has encountered an Error.

PublisherSubscriber.description: Reference to DataSetReader and DataSetWriter required.

CommInitial.description: At least one of the ConnectionEndpoints has its Status set to Initial.

CommPreOperational.description: At least one of the ConnectionEndpoints has its Status set to PreOperational.

CommError.description: At least one of the ConnectionEndpoints has its Status set to Error.
